## `GET /sources/{sourceSchema}/{sourceTable}/freshness`

Check source freshness

Evaluates whether a source relation is fresh based on its max timestamp lag.

- Operation ID: `checkSourceFreshness`

### Path Parameters

| Name | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `sourceSchema` | `string` | `true` | Schema name for the source relation. |
| `sourceTable` | `string` | `true` | Table name for the source relation. |

### Query Parameters

| Name | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `max_lag_seconds` | `integer` | `false` | Maximum allowed lag in seconds before source is considered stale. |
| `timestamp_column` | `string` | `false` | Optional timestamp column to evaluate. If omitted, common timestamp columns are auto-detected. |

### Responses

| Code | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `200` | Source freshness status |

| `401` | Authentication credentials are missing or invalid. |
| `404` | The requested resource was not found. |
| `429` | Rate limit exceeded. Retry after the indicated duration. |
| `500` | An unexpected internal server error occurred. |
